article.description: — Kaleb Scott's 22 points and 12 rebounds helped Presbyterian defeat Johnson & Wales (NC) 91-67 on Saturday.
article.headline: Scott has 22 points, 12 rebounds to help Presbyterian beat Johnson & Wales (NC) 91-67
article.linkText: Scott has 22 points, 12 rebounds to help Presbyterian beat Johnson & Wales (NC) 91-67
article.story: CLINTON, S.C. -- — Kaleb Scott's 22 points and 12 rebounds helped Presbyterian defeat Johnson & Wales (NC) 91-67 on Saturday. Marquis Barnett scored 18 points and added six rebounds for the Blue Hose (8-7). Kobe Stewart was 5-of-7 shooting (2 for 3 from 3-point range) to finish with 14 points. Jaden Scriven led the way for the Wildcats with 14 points. Jaben Mars added 12 points and Ethan Smith had eight points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
